XML_TEMPLATES.name: sap.sac.df.FlexAnalysis
XML_TEMPLATES.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new FlexAnalysis. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getShowTitle showTitle} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getAutoUpdate autoUpdate} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getConfigurationURI configurationURI} : string
    • {@link #getConfigObject configObject} : object
    • {@link #getConfigId configId} : string
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: "100%")
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: "100%")
    • {@link #getHideDesignPanel hideDesignPanel} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideStylePanel hideStylePanel} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideMenuBar hideMenuBar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideStatusBar hideStatusBar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideToolBar hideToolBar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideFilterLine hideFilterLine} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getHideSideNavigation hideSideNavigation} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getHideLandingPage hideLandingPage} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSystemName systemName} : string
    • {@link #getDataSource dataSource} : string (default: "$datasource")
    • {@link #getSystemType systemType} : sap.sac.df.types.SystemType (default: BW)
    • {@link #getKeepAliveInterval keepAliveInterval} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getClientIdentifier clientIdentifier} : string
    • {@link #getDataProvider dataProvider} : any
    • {@link #getMultiDimModelId multiDimModelId} : string (default: "om")
    • {@link #getMetaPath metaPath} : string
    • {@link #getImplicitVariableHandling implicitVariableHandling} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getStyleTemplateName styleTemplateName} : string
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCustomPanels customPanels} : sap.ui.core.Control[] (default)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:onCellClick onCellClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
XML_TEMPLATES.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.132 Replaced by {@link sap.sac.df.DataAnalyzer DataAnalyzer} or {@link sap.sac.df.Grid Grid}.
Enables users to view, navigate and change multidimensional data exposed via InA.

Overview

The user can view the data in a Table, navigate in the data via a context menu or builder panels The data source that the FlexAnalysis consumes or renders has to be provided as a property value.

DeprecatedInfo.description: Replaced by {@link sap.sac.df.DataAnalyzer DataAnalyzer} or {@link sap.sac.df.Grid Grid}.

XML_TEMPLATES.name: sap.sac.df.changeHandler.MultiDimModelChangeHandler
XML_TEMPLATES.helpDescription: Control to handle changes of {@link sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel }. To store the changes in {@link sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement} you need to include this change handler control as a dependent somewhere in the view tree for which the variant management is responsible. Each time new data is fetched and the event dataLoaded is fired a new change will be created. The method dataLoaded needs to be called once to register the {@link sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel} to the change handler.
